Alright this is such an abysmal take.

He has two friends, 3.5 by the end of the story. The MTF members all are scared of him. His only friends are Holly and Eleanor because they've interacted with each other for two years. Zimmerman only likes him because Androcles saved his life, even though he had every reason to think he was dead.
Argos is his friend because he was made entirely out of Andy's blood and there's an implied psychic connection.
Hargraves is an opportunistic fuck who only treats Androcles well because he wants to use him for his own personal gain. It's the same amount of respect as a worker and a tool.
Yeah? It's a story about him? I do not see the complaint here.
He's not a  He's a man struggling with the morality of a world completely alien to his own. How does he know what's right? Can he find something worth fighting for? Is the concept of objective good even real?
Yeah, it references Able. But the similarities aren't as immense as you imply. The idea of a perfect soldier or an immortal warrior permeate fiction and Able by no means holds all the cards.








